         <div class="documentTop SubjectPage">            
                     
            <h1>International efforts in relation to indigenous peoples</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"><img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_urfolk150x113.jpg" alt="Samepolitikk
Author: Kenneth Hætta" /></div>
            <p class="textIngress">The Norwegian authorities participate actively in various forums in the field of international 
work relating to indigenous peoples.
</p>
            <img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_urfolk150x113.jpg" alt="Samepolitikk
Author: Kenneth Hætta" class="temaIngressImg" />
            <div class="descriptionText"><p>Norway has played an active part in the establishment of the UN’s permanent forum for indigenous issues, and it has also been part of the working group that drew up the UN declaration on the rights of indigenous peoples. In the far north, the Norwegian authorities take part in the Barents Collaboration and the Arctic Council. Norwegian attitudes to international indigenous issues are formulated in close cooperation with the Sámediggi.</p>
</div>
	    <div style="clear:both"></div>
	      
         </div>
         
         
                                
        
        
        
                            
    <div id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_divPageContent" class="documentBody">  
                

<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_internasjonalt_FNerklaering75x100.gif" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/fad/Selected-topics/Sami-policy/international-efforts-in-relation-to-ind/the-un-declaration-on-the-rights-of-indi.html?id=87024">The UN Declaration on the Rights of Indigenous peoples</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               The UN General Assembly adopted a joint declaration on indigenous peoples on 13. September 2007. The declaration was drawn up in close collaboration between states and various indigenous groups. 
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_FNperm100x75.jpg" alt="Samepolitikk" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/fad/Selected-topics/Sami-policy/international-efforts-in-relation-to-ind/the-uns-permanent-forum-for-indigenous-i.html?id=87026">The UN’s Permanent forum for Indigenous Issues</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               The UN’s Permanent forum for Indigenous Issues is an advisory body to the UN’s Economic and Social Council (ECOSOC). The forum shall give advice and make recommendations in matters that concern indigenous people in the fields of economic and social development, culture, education, health and human rights. Norway has played an active part in the work to establish the indigenous peoples forum.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_internasjonalt_ILO75x100.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/fad/Selected-topics/Sami-policy/international-efforts-in-relation-to-ind/the-ilo-convention-on-the-rights-of-indi.html?id=487963">The ILO Convention on the Rights of Indigenous Peoples</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               The main principle in ILO Convention no. 169 on indigenous peoples and tribal peoples in independent countries is the right of indigenous peoples to further develop their culture and the authorities’ obligation to initiate measures to support this work. Norway ratified the convention in 1990.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_sametinget100x75.jpg" alt="Samepolitikk" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/fad/Selected-topics/Sami-policy/international-efforts-in-relation-to-ind/cooperation-with-the-sami-parliament-on-.html?id=87027">Cooperation with the Sami Parliament on international indigenous issues</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               The Government places great emphasis on discussing and negotiating about indigenous issues through close cooperation between the Government and representatives of indigenous people. Norwegian attitudes to international indigenous issues are therefore formulated in close cooperation with the Sámediggi. 
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    

